    • Method Detail

      • transferFactor

        default int transferFactor()
        Can be used as factor for transferring stacks of a channel. E.g. used by IO Ports to transfer 1000 mB, not 1 mB to match the item channel transferring a full bucket per operation.
        Returns:

      • getUnitsPerByte

        default int getUnitsPerByte()
        The number of units (eg item count, or millibuckets) that can be stored per byte in a storage cell. Standard value for items is 8, and for fluids it's 8000
        Returns:
        number of units

      • createStack

        @Nullable
T createStack(@Nonnull
                        java.lang.Object input)
        Create a new IAEStack subtype of the specific object. The parameter is unbound to allow a slightly more flexible approach. But the general intention is about converting an ItemStack or FluidStack into the corresponding IAEStack. Another valid case might be to use it instead of IAEStack.copy(), but this might not be supported by all types. IAEStacks that use custom items for IAEStack.asItemStackRepresentation() must also be able to convert these.
        Parameters:
        input - The object to turn into an IAEStack
        Returns:
        The converted stack or null
